# cogbot-membership-website-template

A membership-gated website template powered by CogBot chat and IBM App ID authentication. Each deployment is a single client — customize it by editing `site.config.js`.

---

## Architecture

- **React 19 + Vite** — static SPA, no server-side code in this repo
- **Tailwind CSS v3** — styling via CSS custom properties (design tokens in `src/index.css`)
- **React Router v7** — client-side routing (`/` public, `/members` gated)
- **IBM App ID (oidc-client-ts)** — authentication via OIDC popup login
- **CMG (CogBot Membership Gateway)** — external service that validates membership
- **CogBot widget API** — external chat service

Authentication flow:
```
User clicks Sign In
  → App ID popup (OIDC)
  → idToken stored in sessionStorage
  → POST to CMG /auth/validate with { idToken, namespace }
  → CMG returns { isMember, roles, geofenced }
  → ProtectedRoute + RoleGate gate the /members page
```

---

## Where to make changes

### Change site content or branding
Edit `site.config.js` at the project root. This is the ONLY file that differs between clients. It contains every user-visible string: site name, bot name, hero text, features, testimonials, about section, member page copy, footer text.

### Change colors or fonts
Edit the CSS custom properties in `src/index.css` under `:root`. Colors use HSL values:
```css
:root {
  --primary: 197 78% 53%;     /* main brand color */
  --secondary: 2 76% 58%;     /* accent color */
  --accent: 45 95% 62%;       /* highlight color */
}
```

### Change logos or images
Replace files in `public/`. Update the paths in `site.config.js` under `images:`:
- `public/buddy-icon.webp`    — chat avatar and header icon
- `public/bab-full-logo.webp` — "Presented by" logo in the hero
- `public/favicon.svg`        — browser tab icon

### Change auth credentials
Edit `.env`. Never hardcode credentials in source files.

### Add a new page
1. Create `src/pages/MyPage.jsx`
2. Add a route in `src/App.jsx`:
   ```jsx
   <Route path="/my-page" element={<MyPage />} />
   ```
3. To make it member-only, wrap it:
   ```jsx
   <Route path="/my-page" element={
     <ProtectedRoute>
       <RoleGate requiredRole="member">
         <MyPage />
       </RoleGate>
     </ProtectedRoute>
   } />
   ```

---

## File guide

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `site.config.js` | All branding and content — start here for any text or content change |
| `.env` | Service credentials — copy from `.env.example` and fill in values |
| `public/` | Logo and icon images |
| `src/index.css` | Design tokens (colors, fonts) — edit to change the theme |
| `src/App.jsx` | Route definitions — add new pages here |
| `src/components/` | Shared UI components — read from site.config.js |
| `src/pages/` | Page components (LandingPage, MembersPage, etc.) |
| `src/auth/` | Auth modules — do not modify unless changing auth providers |
| `src/services/buddyApi.js` | CogBot API client — do not modify unless changing chat provider |
| `src/hooks/useBuddyChat.js` | Chat state management |
| `vite.config.js` | Build config and dev proxy |

---

## Auth modules (do not modify without good reason)

| File | What it does |
|---|---|
| `src/auth/AuthProvider.jsx` | App ID login/logout, stores user + membership state |
| `src/auth/userManager.js` | Configures oidc-client-ts with App ID OIDC settings |
| `src/auth/ProtectedRoute.jsx` | Shows LoginPage if user is not authenticated |
| `src/auth/RoleGate.jsx` | Shows AccessDenied if user is not a member or lacks required role |
| `src/auth/useAuthorization.js` | Calls CMG /auth/validate, returns membership status and roles |

---

## Deployment

**Platform hosting (Lovable, Vercel, Netlify, etc.):**
- Set all `VITE_*` variables from `.env.example` in your platform's build settings
- Build command: `npm run build`
- Output directory: `dist`

**Running locally:**
```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Fill in .env with your credentials
npm install
npm run dev
```

---

## Common tasks (for AI assistants)

- "Change the hero headline" → edit `hero.tagline` in `site.config.js`
- "Add a testimonial" → add an item to `testimonials.items` in `site.config.js`
- "Change the primary color" → edit `--primary` in `src/index.css`
- "Add a new page" → create in `src/pages/`, register in `src/App.jsx`
- "Change the CogBot" → update `VITE_COGBOT_ID` in `.env`
- "Change the sign-in button label" → edit `header.signInLabel` in `site.config.js`
